org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.cloudformation.mapper

Class CapabilityMapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opentosca.toscana.plugins.cloudformation.mapper.CapabilityMapper

  • public class CapabilityMapper
extends java.lang.Object
    Maps OsCapabilities and ComputeCapabilities to values for CloudFormation.
    It uses the AWS Region and the AWS Credentials to connect to AWS via the AWS SDK to fetch the latest image id suitable for given OsCapability.
    See Also:
    MappingUtils

    • Method Detail

      • mapOsCapabilityToImageId

        public java.lang.String mapOsCapabilityToImageId(OsCapability osCapability)
                                          throws com.amazonaws.SdkClientException,
                                                 java.text.ParseException,
                                                 java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Requests the AWS server for ImageIds with filters which are filled based on the values of the OsCapability.
        The image with the latest creation date is picked and its imageId returned.
        Parameters:
        osCapability - the OsCapability to map
        Returns:
        a String that contains a valid ImageId that can be added to the properties of an EC2
        Throws:
        com.amazonaws.SdkClientException
        java.text.ParseException
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException

      • mapComputeCapabilityToInstanceType

        public java.lang.String mapComputeCapabilityToInstanceType(ComputeCapability computeCapability,
                                                           java.lang.String distinction)
                                                    throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Finds the best CapabilityMapper.InstanceType based on the values contained in the ComputeCapability.
        If necessary the values are scaled upwards till they meet the requirement.
        Parameters:
        computeCapability - the ComputeCapability to map
        distinction - a distinction string, can either be "EC2" or "RDS"
        Returns:
        a valid CapabilityMapper.InstanceType / InstanceClass(RDS) String
        Throws:
        TransformationFailureException - Gets thrown if the values numCpus and memSize are too big and there is no valid CapabilityMapper.InstanceType.
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException

      • mapComputeCapabilityToRDSAllocatedStorage

        public java.lang.Integer mapComputeCapabilityToRDSAllocatedStorage(ComputeCapability computeCapability)
        Takes the value from the ComputeCapability and turns it into GB.
        The minimum is 20 GB the maximum 6144 GB
        Parameters:
        computeCapability - the ComputeCapability to map
        Returns:
        returns an integer representing the diskSize that should be taken
